commit.message: Convert text argument to str automatically.
Formatted code with Black.
Updating tests.
Extended the tests to check native and tkinter versions of the alert() and confirm() tests.
Renamed TIMEOUT_TEXT to TIMEOUT_RETURN_VALUE
Commented out WindowsNativeAlertTests and WindowsNativeConfirmTests because their interfaces might be permanently out of date now.

Changed the names of the functions so that they could work with native functions (this is backwards compatible). Added more *_TEXT constants for Windows button text. Added ability to specify icons in Windows native functions. Set up fallbacks for the Windows native functions to the original tKinter functions.
Updated setup.py to a more modern format (using my cookiecutter-basicpythonproject template) which also solved the issue of not being able to install pymsgbox with 'pip install -e .'
Removing setup.cfg because it was blank and we don't need it.
Removing README.rst
Adding project files.

Deleting the empty native files until we actually need them.

Updated documentation for timeouts.
Added timeout parameter to functions & unit tests for timeout feature. Added constants for 'Ok', 'Cancel', and 'Timeout' for easier localization.

Enabled the dialog windows' close buttons (returns 'Cancel').

Also fixed issue #1.
